Colouration. Dorsal surface light brown to very dark brown, with irregular dark and light flecks or blotches, shading into white ventral surface (
Figure 4
). A white, black-edged “tear-drop” under eye, although this may be indistinct in some animals. Well marked pale dorsolateral stripe from near tip of snout to near midpoint of body, thereafter broken up by brown patches. Throat, chin and belly lightly speckled. There do not appear to be sexually dimorphic colour patterns. Juvenile colouration is unknown.
